Node.Notes: Syntax obscure, but general meaning clear. Command to combine various sources of income (interpreters differ on number) for temple repair. Tree assumes four sources (see WBC commentary).
Literally, money of the holy things (apparently money set aside for the manufacture and purchase of the sacred utensils of the temple).
Literally, the money of the crossing over of a person (apparently background in ex30:13-14, governing the census of Israelites).
Literally, the money of persons, according to his reckoning. Apparently tax levied against persons who offered their services to the temple (cf. Lev 27:1–33).
Apparently voluntary offerings which given on an irregular basis.
